 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Written at her Apartment in Windsor-Castle.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">You, dear Maid, to soft alarms</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Resign the genial hour,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Forsaking all for  charms,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Your own, and Ours no more:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I lean my philosophic head</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">On table cold as clay,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And read — good Gods, how I do read!</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">My very soul away.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">My Lady hears away her rage</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">In tragedy so deep:</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Fringes no more her soul engage —</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Ev'n  has leave to sleep.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thus all forgetting, or forgot,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">While  are from our view,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To knot and read, and read and knot,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Is all we have to do.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
